  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="TK13">
<l>viṇṇiṉṟu poyppiṉ virinīr viyaṉulakat</l>
<l>tuṇṇiṉ ṟuṭaṟṟum paci</l>            
            </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Hunger—as long as clouds fail, so long will it plague us</l>
<l>in this vast world of wide waters.</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
  </text>
  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <head>Parimēlaḻakar</head>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="TK13_P1">
          (i-ḷ). maḻai vēṇṭuṅkālattup peyyātu poykku māyiṉ kaṭalāṟ cūḻappaṭṭa akaṉṟa vulakattiṉkaṇnilaipeṟ ṟuyirkaḷai varuttum paci, (e-ṟu).
        </p>
        <p xml:lang="en">
          The meaning ... : If clouds, during a time when [rain] is needed, fail and do not pour, hunger will become established in the extensive world surrounded by the ocean and torment the living beings in it.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="TK12_P2">
          kaṭaluṭait tāyiṉu mataṉāṟ payaṉillai yeṉpār ‘virinīr viyaṉulakattuḷ’ eṉṟār. uṇaviṉmaiyiṉ paciyā ṉuyirka ḷiṟakkum eṉpatām.
        </p>
        <p xml:lang="en">
          To express that, even if [the world] has the ocean, no fruit comes of it, [the poet] has said "in the vast world of wide waters." [The idea] is that, in the absence of sustenance, living beings will die from hunger.
        </p>
      </div>
    </body>
  </text>
  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <head>Maṇakkuṭavar (14)</head>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="TK13_M1">
          vāṉamāṉatu nilainiṟkap poykkumāyiṉ, virinta nīriṉai yuṭaiya akaṉṟa vulakattiṭattē paciyāṉatu niṉṟu varuttāniṟkum; ellāvuyir kaḷaiyum, (e - ṟu).
        </p>
        <p xml:lang="en">
          If clouds fail to be established(?), hunger will abide right in the midst of the extensive world and continue to torment all living beings(?).
        </p>
      </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="TK13_M2">
          poyttal - taṉṟoḻil maṟuttal. itu ‘paci’ eṉṟu potuppaṭak kūṟiyavataṉāṉ makkaḷum vilaṅkum, poruḷuṅ kāmamun tuykkalāṟṟātu tuṉpa, muṟumeṉṟu kūṟiṟṟu.
        </p>
        <p xml:lang="en">
          To "fail" [means] to reject one's own (proper) function. [In] this [verse], by mentioning "hunger" as a generality, [the poet has effectively] said that people and animals, being unable to satisfy their [needs for] welfare and pleasure, will suffer.
        </p>
      </div>
    </body>
  </text>
